L <- length(Distance)
Dimension <- rep(1, L)
Distance <- c(Distance, as.vector(as.matrix( dist(X[,1:2]) )))
Dimension <- c(Dimension, rep(2, L))
Distance <- c(Distance, as.vector(as.matrix( dist(X[,1:3]) )))
Dimension <- c(Dimension, rep(3, L))
Distance <- c(Distance, as.vector(as.matrix( dist(X[,1:4]) )))
Dimension <- c(Dimension, rep(4, L))
Distance <- as.vector(as.matrix( dist(X[,1]) )) L <- length(Distance) Dimension <- rep(1, L) Distance <- c(Distance, as.vector(as.matrix( dist(X[,1:2]) ))) Dimension <- c(Dimension, rep(2, L)) Distance <- c(Distance, as.vector(as.matrix( dist(X[,1:3]) ))) Dimension <- c(Dimension, rep(3, L)) Distance <- c(Distance, as.vector(as.matrix( dist(X[,1:4]) ))) Dimension <- c(Dimension, rep(4, L))

is contained in the package kernlab. Try out other kernel types beyond the gaussian one. Type help(kpca) to see how to use the options.

     th = 1e-4, 
     na.action = na.omit)

Linear Discriminant Analysis¶

contained in the MASS package. The functions run a regression based on the projection,so we provide prior probabilities for each class (they give weight to each class). formula = Species ~ . means that all the variables apart from thhe species labels are part of the regression (projection)

In [975]:
Copied! 
Y_lda <- lda(formula = Species ~ ., 
          data = iris, 
          prior = c(1,1,1)/3)
Y_lda <- lda(formula = Species ~ ., data = iris, prior = c(1,1,1)/3)

We calculate those features using some good old vectorization in R. First take the coefficients

In [978]:
Copied! 
coeff_LD1 <- matrix(rep(Y_lda$scaling[,"LD1"],dim(X)[1]),
       nrow=dim(X)[1], byrow=T)
coeff_LD1 <- matrix(rep(Y_lda$scaling[,"LD1"],dim(X)[1]), nrow=dim(X)[1], byrow=T)
In [979]:
Copied! 
coeff_LD2 <- matrix(rep(Y_lda$scaling[,"LD2"],dim(X)[1]),
       nrow=dim(X)[1], byrow=T)
coeff_LD2 <- matrix(rep(Y_lda$scaling[,"LD2"],dim(X)[1]), nrow=dim(X)[1], byrow=T)

Then multiply by the data and do the sum by rows

In [980]:
Copied! 
LD1 = rowSums(X * coeff_LD1)
LD1 = rowSums(X * coeff_LD1)
In [981]:
Copied! 
LD2 = rowSums(X * coeff_LD2)
LD2 = rowSums(X * coeff_LD2)

make a proper dataframe and plot

Benchmarking the tSNEs¶

Benchmarking improved tSNE VS tSNE from the book CASL and showing execution time (in seconds)

In [951]:
Copied! 
MB <- microbenchmark("Improved" = { sam_tsne(X_std, init = PCA$ind$coord,
                                    momentum=list(init=.5, final=.9, iter=200L),
                                    early_ex=list(factor=12, iter=200L), 
                                    perplexity = 10, rho=100) },
                     "CASL" =  { casl_tsne(X_std, init = PCA$ind$coord,
                                    perplexity = 20, rho=100) },
                      times=1 )
MB <- microbenchmark("Improved" = { sam_tsne(X_std, init = PCA$ind$coord, momentum=list(init=.5, final=.9, iter=200L), early_ex=list(factor=12, iter=200L), perplexity = 10, rho=100) }, "CASL" = { casl_tsne(X_std, init = PCA$ind$coord, perplexity = 20, rho=100) }, times=1 )
